    <text id="F4016T">
        <front id="d2">
            <div1 type="summary" id="d3">
                <p>McClure's letter expresses confidence that he will win in the upcoming election
                    for the Pennsylvania state legislature.</p>
            </div1>
        </front>

        <body id="d4">
            <div1 type="letter" id="d5">
                <head>McClure &amp; Stoner,<lb/>Publishers<lb/>Franklin Repository
                    Office,<lb/>Chambersburg, <abbr expan="Pennsylvania">Pa.</abbr>
                </head>

                <opener>
                    <dateline>
                        <date value="1864-10-13"><abbr expan="October">Oct</abbr> 13, 1864</date>
                        <name type="place">Chambersburg, <abbr expan="Pennsylvania">Pa.</abbr></name>
                    </dateline>
                    <salute>Dear Sir,</salute>
                </opener>

                <p>Please speak to Mr Espy and engage the best room she has for me this winter. Mrs
                    McClure will be with me most of the time, &amp; I will of course want the
                    best accomodations I can get. Would like a front room on the second floor if
                    possible. Please speak to Mrs Espy at once on the subject before her rooms are
                    taken. I do not care so much about the price as about making Mrs <abbr
                        expan="McClure">McC</abbr> comfortable.</p>

                <p>We had a desperate <unclear>cented</unclear> in this county. We
                        <unclear>Democrats</unclear> stiffened up <unclear>fearfully</unclear>
                    within ten days before the election. They <pb n="2"/>thought they had a chance
                    to defeat me, &amp; they exhausted themselves to do it. I gained some 300 in
                    the county, and have a majority of about 70 in the district <unclear>in the home
                        vote.</unclear> I will have from 200 to 300 in the full vote.</p>

                <p>I infer from the reports that <del rend="none" hand="h1"/> is beaten in the home vote
                    &amp; Hains &amp; Hall also. I telegraphed Curtin to mark for me the
                    seat occupied by Cochran last winter &amp; if that was taken to mark the one
                    along side of it. <hi rend="underline">Please see that it is done.</hi> If both
                    are taken mark a good seat for me <hi rend="underline">next to one of the
                        aisles.</hi></p>

                <closer>
                    <salute>Yours <abbr expan="Truly">T</abbr></salute>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="underline">AKMcClure</hi>
                    </signed>
                    <seg type="postscript">
                        <name type="recipient"><abbr expan="Honorable">Hon</abbr> Eli Slifer</name>
                    </seg>
                </closer>
            </div1>
        </body>
    </text>
